because I put the bomb in the garage.

250
00:22:24,240 --> 00:22:27,800
I don't make fancy bombs.
They're simple little things.

251
00:22:27,920 --> 00:22:31,520
But I know where to put them.
I never meant to kill anybody.

252
00:22:31,640 --> 00:22:34,200
And the twins?

253
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:41,560
- Casualties of war.
- The father losing his legs?

254
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:44,720
- Killing himself?
- I don't want to talk about this.

255
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:47,200
Are you hiding something from me?

256
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:50,360
- I wouldn't advise it.
- I got nothing to hide.

257
00:22:50,480 --> 00:22:53,920
I did what I had to do.
The Klan was at war.

258
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:56,760
We would've won,
but we started bombing the Jews

259
00:22:56,880 --> 00:23:00,400
and with all their money
they got the FBI and they beat us.

260
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:03,160
We should've just stayed
whipping up on the niggers.

261
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:05,520
World would've been a different place.

262
00:23:05,640 --> 00:23:08,240
You can pretend
you're all offended by this.

263
00:23:08,360 --> 00:23:13,800
But, deep down inside, we both know
there's a part of you that agrees with me.

264
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:15,800
That's bullshit.

265
00:23:15,920 --> 00:23:18,240
Why are you getting so touchy?

266
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:20,720
- What are you hiding?
- I'm not hiding a thing.

267
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:22,200
Like hell you're not.

268
00:23:22,320 --> 00:23:25,960
You're driving your car
and some drunk jungle bunny cuts you off,

269
00:23:26,080 --> 00:23:29,440
his ghetto music blastin',
what do you think?

270
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:32,200
"Well, you darned African-American!"

271
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:35,800
No. You think, "Nigger."

272
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:40,440
If you had any guts, you'd say so.

273
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:48,760
I'm gonna come back tomorrow.

274
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:52,280
I hurt your little feelings, have I?

275
00:23:53,680 --> 00:23:55,520
What did you expect to find here?

276
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:58,520
Old Grandpa Do-Good?
Expect me to go all blubbery,

277
00:23:58,640 --> 00:24:01,440
kiss your behind
and sing psalms of forgiveness?

278
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:03,160
I don't know what I expected.

279
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:07,240
Sure you did... grandson.

280
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:27,640
Hi. I'm Nora Stark, Attorney Hall.

281
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:30,360
I kind of clean up
after Governor McAllister.

282
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:33,960
- Adam, please.
- Adam it shall be.

283
00:24:34,080 --> 00:24:35,680
I'm very curious.

284
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:39,800
You know the same points raised in
the pending ineffective counsel petition

285
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:42,560
were turned down by Texas just last month?

286
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:44,880
Actually, I do know. But it's my opinion

287
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:49,000
that Texas is miles ahead of Mississippi
in many things, including stupidity.

288
00:24:49,120 --> 00:24:50,880
I'm optimistic.

289
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:54,840
- Morning, Counsel.
- Morning, Your Honour.

290
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:58,920
This is a serious business.

291
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:03,880
Ultimate, irreversible punishment
of a fellow human.

292
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:07,520
Time is the purest gold.

293
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:11,160
When do you plan to file an appeal?

294
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:15,160
Oddly, I had planned on waiting

295
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:18,440
for the court to issue a ruling
before appealing it,

296
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,080
Your Honour.

297
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:26,560
However, if, as expected... Thursday?

298
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:31,560
- And the State's response?
- We agree.

299
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:36,480
Assuming you'll not be introducing
additional issues on this appeal...

300
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:38,480
Obviously not.

301
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:41,120
...Friday morning.

302
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:44,720
You'll have my decision Friday.

303
00:25:46,120 --> 00:25:49,600
Can the court expect additional filings?

304
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:53,280
Are you asking me
my legal strategy, Your Honour?

305
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:55,320
Not at all, sir.

306
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:58,680
But I'm thrilled to know you have one.

307
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:01,320
Y'all are dismissed. Now.

308
00:26:04,480 --> 00:26:06,480
Carl, Irene, how are you?

309
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:08,720
Adam!

310
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,600
Clemency?

311
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:12,640
Contractually bound not to ask.

312
00:26:12,760 --> 00:26:14,880
You haven't, but you will.

313
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,880
You see, the governor's
a very open-minded man.

314
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:20,160
He's not precluding anything.

315
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:22,600
You becoming a lawyer
must have made Sam proud.

316
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:26,160
You should be familiar
with his view of the profession.

317
00:26:26,280 --> 00:26:30,800
I'd just as soon keep this discussion
on the issue and off the record.

318
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:35,080
I believe you're reconsidering
the state-sanctioned murder of my client.

319
00:26:35,200 --> 00:26:38,280
- Adam, would you mind?
- No, sir.

320
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:42,240
I am obviously extremely proud
to have won a conviction

321
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:45,400
where two previous prosecutors have failed.

322
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:49,240
While I have no doubt
Sam Cayhall is guilty as charged,

323
00:26:49,360 --> 00:26:52,160
I've always doubted he acted alone

324
00:26:52,280 --> 00:26:55,880
and as you know, he's never been inclined
to help himself in that regard.

325
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:58,360
What exactly are you saying?

326
00:26:58,480 --> 00:27:02,720
- Is there something specific you know?
- No, certainly not.

327
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:06,240
I just wanna make sure justice is served.

328
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:09,120
I see.

329
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:11,640
So, if I should somehow learn...

330
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:13,960
Adam, I take my power to decide

331
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:18,040
whether a fellow human
should live or die very seriously.

332
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:22,280
If I could somehow be convinced
your client felt the same way...

333
00:27:22,400 --> 00:27:26,240
I'm sorry to rush. Nora,
help out Mr Hall in every way we can.

334
00:27:26,360 --> 00:27:31,320
- It was lovely to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

335
00:27:33,040 --> 00:27:36,400
Let me guess.
You're not convinced he's sincere.

336
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:39,440
- Allow me a touch of healthy scepticism.
- Of course.

337
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:41,880
However, off the record and on the issue,

338
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:46,160
you're being given the opportunity
to provide the governor with cover.

339
00:27:46,280 --> 00:27:49,800
- I love politics.
- If he stays the execution for no reason,

340
00:27:49,920 --> 00:27:54,320
to the left he's a friend of the old guard,
and to the right he's soft on crime.

341
00:27:54,440 --> 00:27:57,400
And as it was he who won the conviction,

342
00:27:57,520 --> 00:27:59,440
he looks to the world like a flip-flop.

343
00:27:59,560 --> 00:28:02,920
But if I come up with something,
he can follow his conscience.

344
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:05,560
Let's just say it expands his options.

345
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:08,120
So you've been assigned
my new best friend.

346
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:10,480
Something like that.

347
00:28:10,600 --> 00:28:13,280
- I'll win this in the courts.
- Even better.

348
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:16,440
- It's not getting to the governor.
- Now you're talking.

349
00:28:16,560 --> 00:28:20,400
If you need any help,
that's home, that's office.

350
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:23,440
Call me.

351
00:29:09,200 --> 00:29:12,680
I found this in my motel room last night.

352
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:17,840
"Welcome to Dixie. Please try
and leave everything as you found it."

353
00:29:20,280 --> 00:29:25,000
- Sounds like good manners to me.
- It was attached to a fake bomb.

354
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:31,360
What?

355
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:36,280
- What do you think I should do about it?
- I don't give a damn.

356
00:29:36,400 --> 00:29:39,440
I'm thinking about how
that gas I'll be forced to sniff

357
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:44,160
makes your lungs explode
and come flying out your mouth.

358
00:29:47,600 --> 00:29:51,000
What motions are you planning to file?

359
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:56,040
We're going to pursue cruel and unusual.

360
00:29:56,160 --> 00:30:00,000
Three years at Michigan Law
and that's the best you got?

361
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:02,320
In 1984, Mississippi passed a law

362
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:05,440
changing executions
from gas chamber to lethal injection.

363
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:10,480
That law applies to folks sentenced
after nineteen hundred and eighty-four.

364
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:13,360
I was sent up here
in nineteen hundred and eighty.

365
00:30:13,480 --> 00:30:16,960
- Now, what's your point?
- You're up on the law, aren't you?

366
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:21,600
I read all the decisions
of all the dead judges. Same as you.

367
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,880
I write some writs for guys on the row.

368
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:26,520
You got any stays yet?

369
00:30:26,640 --> 00:30:29,920
Then keep your matchbook
law school advice to yourself.

370
00:30:30,040 --> 00:30:33,040
By changing to lethal injection
the state admitted de facto

371
00:30:33,160 --> 00:30:35,680
that the gas chamber is a cruel execution.

372
00:30:35,800 --> 00:30:38,880
May I remind Counsel,
speaking as the gasee,

373
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:41,360
I'll be just as dead one way as the other.

374
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:44,400
Sooner or later, yeah,
but I'll take later as a win.

375
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:48,720
Well, I've been losing
better appeals than this for 16 years.

376
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:54,880
I feel like those white guys that always lose
to the nigger Globetrotters.

377
00:30:56,120 --> 00:30:58,880
Why didn't my dad
get infected with this crap?

378
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:01,800
We're having our Eddie talk,
is that it? Be careful.

379
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:04,280
You destroyed him, you must like that.

380
00:31:04,400 --> 00:31:08,760
I destroyed nothing.
He never tried to understand the Klan.

381
00:31:08,880 --> 00:31:11,280
- We were right.
- You still think so?

382
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:14,520
Look what you got now -
AIDS, drugs, bastard children.

383
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:17,360
- Killer bees.
- Well, they come from Africa!

384
00:31:17,480 --> 00:31:20,640
- South America. Close enough?
- Why are you doing this?

385
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:23,960
Cos my life would be a lot easier
if I could just hate you.

386
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:26,760
But you can't, can you? I'm just too lovable.

387
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:31,840
Well, I'm working on it. Your father kills
himself in front of you when you're ten,

388
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:35,280
then at the funeral you find out
Grandpa's still alive - great!

389
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:39,080
Except he's a racist scumbag baby-killer.
Why is that not comforting?

390
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:42,600
Oh, stop, you're breaking my heart.

391
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:48,360
It was your hate
that drove him away, wasn't it?

392
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:51,760
Eddie was weak.

393
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:55,040
I never laid a hand on him.

394
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:57,680
Never got after him.

395
00:31:57,800 --> 00:32:01,840
Never cared who his friends were.
Not even Quince.

396
00:32:02,120 --> 00:32:04,560
Who?

397
00:32:04,680 --> 00:32:08,320
Quince Lincoln,
a nigger kid Eddie used to play with.

398
00:32:08,440 --> 00:32:10,880
- I've heard that name before.
- It's nothing.

399
00:32:11,000 --> 00:32:14,840
No, he used to mention that name,
he'd have these spells...

400
00:32:14,960 --> 00:32:18,160
- Sergeant Packer!
- ...he'd mumble some story...

401
00:32:18,280 --> 00:32:20,920
It don't mean nothing. Shut up about it.

402
00:32:21,040 --> 00:32:26,040
- Who's Quince?
- It don't mean nothing! Shut up about it!

403
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:29,760
Let's go, Sam.

404
00:32:32,800 --> 00:32:35,640
Come on.

405
00:32:39,360 --> 00:32:41,600
- Yep?
- Were you asleep?

406
00:32:41,720 --> 00:32:43,120
No, I'm up.

407
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:47,760
The court's going to reject
ineffective counsel.

408
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:49,480
Yeah, I expected that.

409
00:32:49,600 --> 00:32:54,240
I'll be ready to file the appeal in
New Orleans when the court here rules.

410
00:32:54,360 --> 00:32:59,080
<i>I'll expect your first draft
in the morning. Good night.</i>

411
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:18,880
<i>- Hello?
- Nora?</i>

412
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:20,480
Hi.

413
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:22,800
Does the offer to help still stand?

414
00:33:22,920 --> 00:33:24,760
<i>Sure.</i>

415
00:33:24,880 --> 00:33:29,800
I need to track down the FBI agent
who was in charge of Sam's case.

416
00:33:31,200 --> 00:33:34,080
Sam was of no concern to us,
you understand?

417
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:38,440
He wasn't active in the really nasty stuff
so we didn't track him.

418
00:33:38,560 --> 00:33:41,440
When did that change?

419
00:33:41,560 --> 00:33:45,920
When the civil rights workers disappeared,
Hoover sent us in.

420
00:33:46,040 --> 00:33:47,960
We spread money all over the place.

421
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:51,720
Those people were basically
ignorant rednecks, you know?

422
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:55,400
Didn't have a dime, so we preyed on
their craving for money.

423
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:58,560
Go on.

424
00:33:58,680 --> 00:34:02,240
There's things I can talk about
and things I can't talk about.

425
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:07,080
And some things I won't talk about
cos I don't like you lawyers twisting the truth,

426
00:34:07,200 --> 00:34:10,120
getting killers off
on some legal technicality.

427
00:34:10,240 --> 00:34:12,320
That's bullshit.

428
00:34:12,440 --> 00:34:15,280
Besides, it's too late
for new information, kid.

429
00:34:15,400 --> 00:34:18,040
Courts won't hear it, you know that.

430
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:21,000
Courts don't have
the final say in this case.

431
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:23,840
You said he wasn't involved
in the really nasty stuff.

432
00:34:23,960 --> 00:34:28,280
- He didn't mean to kill.
- Of course he meant to kill.

433
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:31,240
Marvin Kramer was a creature of habit.

434
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:34,680
He was in that office every morning
before eight o'clock.

435
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:37,320
The bomb went off straight up at eight.

436
00:34:37,440 --> 00:34:40,120
The timer was set for eight.

437
00:34:40,800 --> 00:34:47,000
- That was never introduced to trial.
- I can't help that, it was in our report.

438
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:51,280
- I'd like to see that report.
- I can't help you, pal.

439
00:34:51,400 --> 00:34:56,160
I'm just a fisherman now...
who'd just as soon see him gassed.

440
00:34:56,400 --> 00:35:00,040
I've been around those violent assholes
all my life.

441
00:35:00,160 --> 00:35:02,680
Let them taste the other end of violence.

442
00:35:02,800 --> 00:35:06,480
See how brave they are without their hoods.

443
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:11,840
You know what I'm talking about.

444
00:35:13,760 --> 00:35:17,360
Why would our FBI friend not wanna
tell us about a 30-year-old case?

445
00:35:17,480 --> 00:35:20,480
Cos you're in Mississippi now,
land of secrets.

446
00:35:20,600 --> 00:35:23,200
There are bodies buried everywhere.

447
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:28,160
But no one's hiding anything -
they don't have to, Sam did it.

448
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:32,400
They just don't want you looking because
they're not sure what might turn up.

449
00:35:32,520 --> 00:35:36,040
- Who is "they"?
