It was an official state agency

456
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:07,040
dedicated to states' rights,
i.e. Fighting civil rights.

457
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:10,440
Some people think it coordinated
the White Citizens' Councils.

458
00:36:10,560 --> 00:36:13,160
- What were those?
- Every town had one.

459
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:16,440
A local group of respectable white people.

460
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:18,480
Professional types.

461
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:23,320
Pillars of their community...
who told the Klan what to do.

462
00:36:24,200 --> 00:36:26,760
So somebody like Sam
wasn't making decisions?

463
00:36:26,880 --> 00:36:30,280
Like our FBI friend said,

464
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:35,040
they were poor, uneducated bigots
who couldn't find their butts with a map.

465
00:36:35,160 --> 00:36:38,200
The Citizens' Councils used them
to do their dirty work.

466
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:43,200
- And the Sovereignty Commission?
- Kept the records.

467
00:36:44,480 --> 00:36:47,360
- Please sign this.
- I ain't signing nothing.

468
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:50,000
The files are sealed by the state legislature.

469
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:54,040
As a defendant, only you can apply
to have your files opened.

470
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:56,720
You're set to die in 20 days,
this might help.

471
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:59,640
- Help him maybe, not me.
- Help who?

472
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:02,760
The governor, you dumbass.
Can't you see it?

473
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:07,200
He can't open the files so he gets you
to do it for him. To help me?

474
00:37:07,320 --> 00:37:09,400
No, he put me here.

475
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:14,400
No, he's just fishing
for political dirt on his enemies.

476
00:37:15,040 --> 00:37:18,200
What's in those files, Sam?

477
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:22,800
Nothing for you. Stuff they'd twist around
and use to hurt my people.

478
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:27,160
I'm your people. Don't you get it? I am.

479
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:31,680
You ain't my real people,
you ain't never met my real people.

480
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:36,240
I don't know how they got the story.

481
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:39,960
<i>It's only a matter of time
before they get around to me.</i>

482
00:37:40,080 --> 00:37:43,640
I am sorry, but listen,
I think I might be onto something.

483
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:47,120
- Some leads from way back.
- Adam, leave it alone.

484
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:50,400
Lee, I really think I can save him.

485
00:37:51,200 --> 00:37:53,880
Ever occur to you
he might not be worth saving?

486
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,280
You can't mean that.

487
00:37:56,400 --> 00:38:00,360
All right, Adam,
you wanna know about the past?

488
00:38:01,400 --> 00:38:04,200
I'll tell you about the past.

489
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:20,720
This was my tree.

490
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:29,960
My own laurel tree.

491
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:36,320
I was up there.

492
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:42,680
Your father was there...

493
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:45,360
with Quince.

494
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:50,440
They were eight, maybe nine.
And they were best friends.

495
00:39:55,440 --> 00:39:59,040
They were fighting, and they made
so much noise Daddy heard

496
00:39:59,160 --> 00:40:02,760
and come out to see
what all the ruckus was.

497
00:40:03,200 --> 00:40:06,120
Go on, go on! Get away home!

498
00:40:06,240 --> 00:40:09,640
Quince's father did day work for Daddy.

499
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:11,320
His name was Joe.

500
00:40:11,440 --> 00:40:14,240
Daddy never was very handy
at mechanical things

501
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:16,720
so Joe fixed things for us, made things.

502
00:40:16,840 --> 00:40:19,640
He was here, all the time.

503
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:24,200
So then Quince came back with his father.

504
00:40:24,800 --> 00:40:27,480
My boy says you been beatin' on him.

505
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:30,640
They fought so hard, like animals.

506
00:40:30,760 --> 00:40:36,480
At one point Daddy grabbed the rake...
and things got out of hand.

507
00:40:37,240 --> 00:40:40,320
He knocked Joe over, Joe fell to the ground,

508
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:43,400
and he yelled for Quince to get his shotgun.

509
00:40:43,520 --> 00:40:48,280
- Quince, get my shotgun!
- Sam told Eddie to get his. Eddie froze.

510
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:51,480
But Daddy made him go.

511
00:40:51,600 --> 00:40:55,400
Joe was here.

512
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:58,120
Daddy was there.

513
00:40:58,240 --> 00:40:59,640
Get in the house.

514
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:02,320
<i>- Joe waited for his gun.
- Get!</i>

515
00:41:02,440 --> 00:41:05,120
He kept looking around.

516
00:41:05,240 --> 00:41:07,440
Sam had his.

517
00:41:07,560 --> 00:41:12,120
And then my dear, sweet father...

518
00:41:33,920 --> 00:41:37,520
This was Mississippi...

519
00:41:37,760 --> 00:41:40,560
in the early '50s.

520
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:45,320
Daddy said self-defence.

521
00:41:45,440 --> 00:41:49,480
He was never even so much as arrested.

522
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:54,360
What were my dad and Quince
fighting about?

523
00:41:58,840 --> 00:42:00,600
A toy soldier.

524
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:03,640
<i>Eddie thought Quince had stolen it.</i>

525
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:07,240
<i>And that night he found it under his bed.</i>

526
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:12,000
He took the weight of the world
on his shoulders.

527
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:15,200
And then he said

528
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:20,080
I had killed Joe Lincoln too.

529
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:29,640
Said if I had cried out for Daddy to stop...

530
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:33,600
no way would he have fired.

531
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:37,600
Not with his sweet baby girl watching.

532
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:44,240
Course, he was right.

533
00:42:48,080 --> 00:42:50,880
It was my fault too.

534
00:43:08,000 --> 00:43:10,960
<i>Get away home.</i>

535
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:35,360
<i>Daddy never was very handy
at mechanical things...</i>

536
00:43:35,480 --> 00:43:38,080
Jesus.

537
00:43:40,520 --> 00:43:45,560
The superintendent asked
if you'd thought about your last meal.

538
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:48,760
Special requests can take time.

539
00:43:48,880 --> 00:43:54,680
Yeah, I want a bowl of Eskimo Pies
and French Market coffee.

540
00:43:54,800 --> 00:43:57,360
It shall be done.

541
00:43:57,480 --> 00:44:02,400
There's been five executions here -
you know of any problems with them?

542
00:44:02,520 --> 00:44:07,000
Come on. They all died within 50 feet of me.

543
00:44:07,120 --> 00:44:10,080
Everybody on the row knows
about every killing.

544
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:14,200
Tell me about Teddy Meeks, then.
Every detail.

545
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:20,640
They didn't know what they were doing.
Everything went wrong.

546
00:44:21,720 --> 00:44:24,080
- Have you seen the chamber?
- Not yet.

547
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:26,760
There's a little room
where the executioner goes

548
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:31,360
to mix up his solution of sulphuric acid.

549
00:44:31,480 --> 00:44:35,480
With Meeks, the executioner was drunk.

550
00:44:35,600 --> 00:44:38,480
- Come on.
- He was drunk.

551
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:42,200
Anyway...

552
00:44:43,800 --> 00:44:47,080
his first batch of brew didn't work.

553
00:44:47,200 --> 00:44:50,320
Meeks held his breath
for as long as he could,

554
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:53,480
then he inhaled and nothing happened.

555
00:44:53,760 --> 00:44:57,360
So they waited.
Meeks waited, the witnesses waited.

556
00:44:57,480 --> 00:45:01,600
Slowly they turned toward
the executioner - who's waiting.

557
00:45:01,720 --> 00:45:03,200
And cussing.

558
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:06,800
He finally goes back
and he mixes up another batch.

559
00:45:06,920 --> 00:45:11,680
He pulls the lever and the acid drops down
where it's supposed to.

560
00:45:11,840 --> 00:45:15,680
He pulls the second lever
that drops in the cyanide pellets.

561
00:45:15,800 --> 00:45:20,240
Sure enough this gas
starts drifting upward...

562
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:24,480
to where old Teddy
is holding his breath again.

563
00:45:27,400 --> 00:45:30,680
Then he finally...
He sucks in a whole noseful of it

564
00:45:30,800 --> 00:45:34,000
and starts shaking and jerking.

565
00:45:34,160 --> 00:45:41,280
There's a metal pole that runs from
the top of the chamber down to the bottom

566
00:45:41,400 --> 00:45:44,120
and it's directly behind the chair.

567
00:45:44,240 --> 00:45:47,040
And...

568
00:45:53,200 --> 00:45:56,280
And just about the time Meeks got real still

569
00:45:56,400 --> 00:45:58,840
and everybody thought he was dead

570
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:02,040
his head starts banging
back and forth against that pole.

571
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:05,880
Just beating the hell out of it, like that.

572
00:46:06,480 --> 00:46:08,560
His eyes were rolled up in his head,

573
00:46:08,680 --> 00:46:13,520
and his lips opened up real wide
and he was foaming at the mouth.

574
00:46:13,760 --> 00:46:16,560
And there he was...

575
00:46:17,280 --> 00:46:21,600
just banging the back of his head
against that pole.

576
00:46:23,720 --> 00:46:26,520
It was sick.

577
00:46:27,400 --> 00:46:29,160
How long did it take them to kill him?

578
00:46:29,280 --> 00:46:34,600
According to the prison doctor,
death was instant and painless.

579
00:46:34,720 --> 00:46:38,440
Packer told me it was the longest
five minutes of his life.

580
00:46:38,560 --> 00:46:43,640
The guy convulsed and heaved
and pounded his skull for so long

581
00:46:43,760 --> 00:46:48,000
that pieces of his brain
was flying out the top of his head.

582
00:47:01,800 --> 00:47:05,920
How does this lever they pull
activate the cyanide canister?

583
00:47:06,040 --> 00:47:09,520
- What?
- The lever! Is it hinges? Springs?

584
00:47:09,640 --> 00:47:12,000
- I don't know.
- Is it just gravity?

585
00:47:12,120 --> 00:47:14,040
How the hell would I know that?

586
00:47:14,160 --> 00:47:16,680
Just thought you had an aptitude for this.

587
00:47:16,800 --> 00:47:19,120
Well, sue me.

588
00:47:19,240 --> 00:47:22,680
- I'm not mechanical.
- That's what Lee said.

589
00:47:22,800 --> 00:47:25,840
But you were handy enough to build
a bomb to kill the Kramers.

590
00:47:25,960 --> 00:47:28,720
Son of a bitch. Is that what this is all about?

591
00:47:28,840 --> 00:47:33,040
You must have stayed up
all night thinking of this one.

592
00:47:33,160 --> 00:47:34,880
Sorry, bubba.

593
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:39,360
Hate to disappoint you
but bombs ain't that complicated.

594
00:47:39,480 --> 00:47:42,000
It can't be that easy - I couldn't do it.

595
00:47:42,120 --> 00:47:44,400
That's because you're not motivated.

596
00:47:44,520 --> 00:47:47,240
By the time I did Kramer
I had it down real simple.

597
00:47:47,360 --> 00:47:51,280
So just because you're an anti-Semite
you can build a bomb,

598
00:47:51,400 --> 00:47:55,040
place it on the second floor,
light a fuse and get out with no risk?

599
00:47:55,160 --> 00:47:58,240
Plenty of risk. Not much glory.

600
00:47:58,360 --> 00:48:02,000
It was the first floor.
Bomb went off below 'em.

601
00:48:02,120 --> 00:48:04,120
- Check the FBI report.
- I did.

602
00:48:04,240 --> 00:48:08,080
- What did it say?
- Bomb went off below 'em.

603
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:11,600
Thank you.
Anything else I can help you with?

604
00:48:11,720 --> 00:48:15,000
- How long was the fuse?
- For Pete's sake...

605
00:48:15,120 --> 00:48:18,240
It happened a long time ago,
I'm an old man.

606
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:20,560
Get off my back here, will you?

607
00:48:20,680 --> 00:48:23,720
I'm sure you can remember
killing two children.

608
00:48:23,840 --> 00:48:26,840
Long enough for me
to get the hell out of there, OK?

609
00:48:26,960 --> 00:48:31,400
Except for one thing - the bomb
didn't have a fuse, it had a timer.

610
00:48:31,520 --> 00:48:36,240
- What are you saying?
- You weren't alone.

611
00:48:36,360 --> 00:48:40,040
There's not a chance
you could have built a timing device.

612
00:48:40,160 --> 00:48:42,680
The FBI searched your house, your garage,

613
00:48:42,800 --> 00:48:46,440
and didn't find a single trace
of explosives anywhere.

614
00:48:46,560 --> 00:48:49,360
Maybe they're stupid.

615
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:53,160
Maybe I was real careful
and didn't leave a trail.

616
00:48:53,680 --> 00:48:56,360
Maybe someone else planted the bomb.

617
00:49:02,400 --> 00:49:06,240
You have no idea what you're doing.

618
00:49:08,160 --> 00:49:11,200
Just hear me out.
Sam couldn't construct a timer.

619
00:49:11,320 --> 00:49:14,320
His bombs were crude,
they had fuses. This was different.

620
00:49:14,440 --> 00:49:17,880
It was complex for back then,
it was timed to kill.

621
00:49:18,000 --> 00:49:21,640
- OK, wait a minute...
- Sam did not plant that bomb.

622
00:49:21,760 --> 00:49:24,920
Wait!

623
00:49:26,600 --> 00:49:31,880
The Sovereignty Commission file on
Sam might say who made the decisions.

624
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:35,400
Adam, just stop this, OK?
Those files are sealed.

625
00:49:35,520 --> 00:49:39,040
If your client won't sign,
you cannot move the court to unseal them.

626
00:49:39,160 --> 00:49:41,800
- I bet you could get a peek at them.
- No.

627
00:49:41,920 --> 00:49:44,240
- You wanted to help me.
- I am helping you.

628
00:49:44,360 --> 00:49:47,880
- Maybe you need to do more.
- Well, maybe I can't!

629
00:49:48,000 --> 00:49:52,920
If there's others
and you're involved in protecting them...

630
00:49:54,360 --> 00:49:55,880
Are you threatening me?

631
00:49:56,000 --> 00:49:59,520
I am pursuing the truth
by any means necessary.

632
00:50:04,240 --> 00:50:08,760
Which includes politely asking for your help.

633
00:50:15,560 --> 00:50:16,880
In addition to appealing cruel and unusual,

634
00:50:17,000 --> 00:50:20,480
- I want to file a new motion.
- About time you focused on the law, bubba.

635
00:50:20,600 --> 00:50:22,920
I never stopped, bubba.

636
00:50:23,040 --> 00:50:26,440
But there is nothing I will not pursue
in order to get a stay,

637
00:50:26,560 --> 00:50:28,280
including proving you're insane.

638
00:50:28,400 --> 00:50:30,640
- I'm insane?
- That's right.

639
00:50:30,760 --> 00:50:33,480
As a product of three generations
of Klan mentality

640
00:50:33,600 --> 00:50:37,840
your indoctrination
into a world of hate born of irrational fear

641
00:50:37,960 --> 00:50:41,840
resulted in diminished mental capacity
to determine right from wrong.

642
00:50:41,960 --> 00:50:45,880
You're gonna argue I'm insane
because I held different political beliefs

643
00:50:46,000 --> 00:50:47,760
than you and your father

644
00:50:47,880 --> 00:50:51,600
and his naive, nigger-loving,
bleeding heart bullshit?

645
00:50:51,720 --> 00:50:55,760
I probably won't use
those exact words in my brief.

646
00:50:56,000 --> 00:50:58,120
I'll wait for the psychiatrist's report.

647
00:50:58,240 --> 00:51:00,760
So I'm gonna see a psychiatrist?

648
00:51:00,880 --> 00:51:03,320
- That's right.
- That's insane.

649
00:51:03,440 --> 00:51:08,760
Killing children whose father was working
for civil rights is insane.

650
00:51:08,880 --> 00:51:10,960
I never meant to kill those kids.

651
00:51:11,080 --> 00:51:16,280
That's fine but you're scheduled
to be executed for it in 14 days.

652
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:23,600
OK.

653
00:51:23,840 --> 00:51:26,640
Good.

654
00:51:28,280 --> 00:51:30,880
I need to go over more family background.

655
00:51:31,000 --> 00:51:35,520
I got some from Lee
but there's a lot of holes in it.

656
00:51:52,000 --> 00:51:55,560
She's going through a tough time right now.

657
00:51:55,800 --> 00:52:00,080
I tried to call her when I saw this
but she didn't answer.

658
00:52:02,120 --> 00:52:05,040
I think she's drinking again.

659
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:10,120
Did you know she's an alcoholic?

660
00:52:15,600 --> 00:52:19,760
Have you ever felt feelings of remorse
for any of your crimes?

661
00:52:19,880 --> 00:52:22,680
No.

662
00:52:23,520 --> 00:52:27,400
Have you ever apologised
to your victims' family?

663
00:52:29,560 --> 00:52:32,320
No, what would be the point?

664
00:52:33,640 --> 00:52:37,200
What do you think would be the point?

665
00:52:37,400 --> 00:52:40,160
No point.

666
00:53:06,960 --> 00:53:10,360
Packer.

667
00:53:10,720 --> 00:53:15,440
I want you to know that
when I talk about your people I...

668
00:53:17,000 --> 00:53:20,200
Well...

669
00:53:21,240 --> 00:53:24,520
I hear you, Sam.

670
00:54:42,240 --> 00:54:47,680
<i>In your professional opinion,
does Sam Cayhall have a conscience?</i>

671
00:54:47,800 --> 00:54:49,760
I found no evidence of one.

672
00:54:49,880 --> 00:54:53,200
Dr Biddows,
is Sam Cayhall in touch with reality?

673
00:54:53,320 --> 00:54:54,800
No, he is not.

674
00:54:54,920 --> 00:54:59,920
Thank you, Dr Biddows.
No further questions, Your Honour.

675
00:55:01,240 --> 00:55:03,120
What sayeth the state?

676
00:55:03,240 --> 00:55:06,440
The state calls Sergeant Clyde Packer.

677
00:55:09,440 --> 00:55:14,840
Sergeant, inform us how long you have
held your present position, please.

678
00:55:14,960 --> 00:55:19,120
Been running the row for 15 years, sir.
Sam's been with me the whole time.

679
00:55:19,240 --> 00:55:23,560
During this time have you ever observed
Mr Cayhall demonstrate

680
00:55:23,680 --> 00:55:28,080
he might have a conscience
or care about other people's feelings?

681
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:29,920
Oh, yes, sir. Everybody knows

682
00:55:30,040 --> 00:55:33,200
Sam has a real bad attitude
toward black folk.

683
00:55:33,320 --> 00:55:37,280
But the other night he told me,
when he says stuff like that...

684
00:55:37,400 --> 00:55:40,880
Let's just say he tried to apologise,
and he didn't even get it all out.

685
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:45,720
And it sure don't make him no saint
but for Sam that's a big deal.

686
00:55:45,840 --> 00:55:48,760
He most certainly do
has a conscience, yes, sir.

687
00:55:48,880 --> 00:55:53,400
And during all this time that
you've been observing him so closely

688
00:55:53,520 --> 00:55:56,520
would you say he knows
what's going on around him?

689
00:55:56,640 --> 00:56:00,880
Would you say he's out of touch with reality?

690
00:56:02,040 --> 00:56:05,000
Two nights back I was walking past
and he said, "Clyde."

691
00:56:05,120 --> 00:56:08,640
He never called me that before
so I knew it was important.

692
00:56:08,760 --> 00:56:10,880
Could I help? "With what, Sam?"

693
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:15,560
And he said, "I wanna die alone.
And I wanna die in decent clothes.

694
00:56:15,680 --> 00:56:20,600
And I wanna eat an Eskimo Pie.
And could I see a sunrise?"

695
00:56:20,720 --> 00:56:24,000
I said, "Last one's on me, Sam."

696
00:56:24,880 --> 00:56:28,480
So I snuck him out, gave him an hour alone.

697
00:56:28,600 --> 00:56:32,800
I watched from inside, I thought he might
lose it once the sun came.

698
00:56:32,920 --> 00:56:38,000
See, it's been 15-16 years
since Sam last saw dawn break

699
00:56:38,120 --> 00:56:40,080
but he held together just fine.

700
00:56:40,200 --> 00:56:43,840
In your opinion,
based on your observations,

701
00:56:43,960 --> 00:56:47,000
is Sam Cayhall in touch with reality?

702
00:56:47,120 --> 00:56:48,480
Sam?

703
00:56:48,600 --> 00:56:51,680
- You betcha.
- Thank you, Sergeant Packer.

704
00:56:51,800 --> 00:56:53,320
Thank you.

705
00:56:53,440 --> 00:56:56,240
Tender the witness, Your Honour.

706
00:56:58,680 --> 00:57:02,920
- What's happening in the Fifth Circuit?
- Thumbs down on insanity.

707
00:57:03,040 --> 00:57:04,960
Hi. There you are.

708
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:07,600
- What's Mr Hall been up to?
- No change.

709
00:57:07,720 --> 00:57:09,880
Try again. What has he been working on?

710
00:57:10,000 --> 00:57:13,680
- He's looking for new information.
- What kind of information?

711
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:16,920
- Nora?
- Sir?

712
00:57:19,600 --> 00:57:21,520
You're not sleeping with him?

713
00:57:21,640 --> 00:57:23,240
No!

714
00:57:23,360 --> 00:57:25,520
Then what kind of information?

715
00:57:25,640 --> 00:57:27,800
Anything, everything. He's desperate.

716
00:57:27,920 --> 00:57:30,720
Where is he looking?

717
00:57:31,160 --> 00:57:33,240
- I don't know.
- Find out.

718
00:57:33,360 --> 00:57:36,400
Desperate people are dangerous.

719
00:57:36,600 --> 00:57:40,160
Maybe you ought to be sleeping with him.

720
00:57:45,480 --> 00:57:46,880
Hey.

721
00:57:47,000 --> 00:57:49,480
- Can we talk?
- Sure.

722
00:57:51,320 --> 00:57:54,240
Tammy?

723
00:58:01,400 --> 00:58:04,760
The Sovereignty Commission
files the originals under lock and key

724
00:58:04,880 --> 00:58:06,640
in the Hall of Records.

725
00:58:06,760 --> 00:58:09,680
Why can't zoning reports wait for tomorrow?

726
00:58:09,800 --> 00:58:12,120
You ask the governor. I like my job.

727
00:58:12,240 --> 00:58:14,160
Nora...

728
00:58:14,280 --> 00:58:18,040
Nora, Nora. It's you that I'm scared of.

729
00:58:18,160 --> 00:58:21,440
Bing, please -
I've got to get this done tonight.

730
00:58:21,560 --> 00:58:24,360
I'll lock up for you.

731
00:58:28,320 --> 00:58:30,480
Our little secret.

732
00:58:30,600 --> 00:58:33,800
You and me. Have a good evening!

733
00:58:55,800 --> 00:58:58,600
This way.

734
00:59:47,840 --> 00:59:51,080
Sovereignty Commissions.

735
01:00:11,520 --> 01:00:15,280
White Citizens' Council, Indianola.

736
01:00:18,520 --> 01:00:21,360
Go back.

737
01:00:32,760 --> 01:00:35,920
- "MK situation should be followed."
- Marvin Kramer.

738
01:00:36,040 --> 01:00:38,120
Or Martin King.

739
01:00:38,240 --> 01:00:41,240
"Law Office, March 18th." Marvin Kramer.
When was the bombing?

740
01:00:41,360 --> 01:00:44,360
April 28th.

741
01:00:46,920 --> 01:00:50,160
"Action agreed September 2nd."
You said it was in April.

742
01:00:50,280 --> 01:00:54,160
That's not a date, that's nine to two -
they took a vote.

743
01:00:54,280 --> 01:00:56,440
- Oh, my God.
- "The Commission assigned SC."

744
01:00:56,560 --> 01:01:00,120
Sam Cayhall. What's RW?

745
01:01:00,320 --> 01:01:03,120
You mean, who's RW?

746
01:01:17,680 --> 01:01:20,080
Thanks.

747
01:01:26,640 --> 01:01:28,560
Truth time, Sam. Five days.

748
01:01:28,680 --> 01:01:33,240
We're firing everything
up to the Supreme Court but...

749
01:01:34,640 --> 01:01:37,920
I need to know who RW is.

750
01:01:41,960 --> 01:01:46,520
Sam, I saw the Commission's files,
you were with someone named RW.

751
01:01:46,640 --> 01:01:48,960
You were assigned to bomb the office

752
01:01:49,080 --> 01:01:52,440
by people who took no responsibility
for the death of those kids

753
01:01:52,560 --> 01:01:56,520
and are gonna take
no responsibility for yours.

754
01:01:57,480 --> 01:02:01,080
I believe you call these people cowards?

755
01:02:01,200 --> 01:02:05,720
Why you feel compelled to protect them
is beyond me.

756
01:02:07,640 --> 01:02:10,440
First of all...

757
01:02:11,000 --> 01:02:14,880
you snivelling little son of a bitch,
you speak to me like this again,

758
01:02:15,000 --> 01:02:18,720
I'll rip your heart out
and shove it up your butt.

759
01:02:18,840 --> 01:02:22,040
Second, if you spent half as much time
learning to be a lawyer

760
01:02:22,160 --> 01:02:25,080
instead of playing Dick Tracy...

761
01:02:25,200 --> 01:02:29,240
I might stand a chance
of not being dead in five days.

762
01:02:29,440 --> 01:02:33,760
As it stands right now
everything you've tried has failed.

763
01:02:34,440 --> 01:02:36,200
You've failed.

764
01:02:36,320 --> 01:02:39,120
Now I have to pay the price.

765
01:02:40,520 --> 01:02:44,240
You're a failure,
just like your pathetic father was!

766
01:02:44,360 --> 01:02:47,040
That son of a bitch
didn't have the balls to live.

767
01:02:47,160 --> 01:02:49,120
He was a loser and a quitter,

768
01:02:49,240 --> 01:02:51,960
and he just gave his life away.

769
01:02:52,080 --> 01:02:54,880
How dare he?

770
01:02:55,320 --> 01:02:59,040
What right did he have to do that?
It wasn't his to give!

771
01:02:59,160 --> 01:03:01,960
I gave it to him! His momma gave it to him!

772
01:03:02,080 --> 01:03:04,280
It was God's! He had no right!

773
01:03:04,400 --> 01:03:07,720
He just gave it away, goddamn it!
He gave it away!

774
01:03:07,840 --> 01:03:10,600
Dammit, he gave it away!

775
01:03:10,720 --> 01:03:13,240
- Why'd he do that?
- Come on.

776
01:03:13,360 --> 01:03:16,240
He gave it away!

777
01:03:27,120 --> 01:03:29,480
- Is she home?
- Miss Lee's resting,

778
01:03:29,600 --> 01:03:32,720
she can't see you now...

779
01:03:32,840 --> 01:03:35,640
Lee?

780
01:03:36,800 --> 01:03:39,120
Where are you, Lee?

781
01:03:39,240 --> 01:03:42,040
Lee?

782
01:03:42,720 --> 01:03:45,520
Lee?

783
01:03:47,080 --> 01:03:50,000
Lee?

784
01:03:56,480 --> 01:03:59,520
Oh, Jesus.

785
01:04:11,240 --> 01:04:14,200
My lucky little nephew.

786
01:04:20,040 --> 01:04:23,080
Did I ever show you...

787
01:04:23,200 --> 01:04:26,880
my favourite old family picture?

788
01:04:29,440 --> 01:04:34,040
Come on. Come in.

789
01:04:38,520 --> 01:04:41,920
I never kept an actual photo album.

790
01:04:42,680 --> 01:04:46,680
Mostly because I never kept
any actual photos.

791
01:04:46,920 --> 01:04:49,720
Here. Come here.

792
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:58,800
Here. Now, there.

793
01:04:59,560 --> 01:05:05,040
See? He was a cute little thing. Wasn't he?

794
01:05:06,280 --> 01:05:08,880
Problem is...

795
01:05:09,000 --> 01:05:12,600
he was raised to be a monster.

796
01:05:16,840 --> 01:05:20,120
Trained from birth.

797
01:05:24,840 --> 01:05:30,040
We come from a long line of hate, Adam.

798
01:05:31,320 --> 01:05:34,120
That's why I drink.

799
01:05:34,360 --> 01:05:37,480
Make it all go away.

800
01:05:38,200 --> 01:05:43,840
Now you're here
and it won't go away any more.

801
01:05:48,600 --> 01:05:52,000
Go home!

802
01:06:06,880 --> 01:06:08,720
I've got three things to say to you.

803
01:06:08,840 --> 01:06:12,200
One, I'm your lawyer until you fire me.
I'm not quitting.

804
01:06:12,320 --> 01:06:14,720
Two, when you killed Joe Lincoln

805
01:06:14,840 --> 01:06:17,520
your seven-year-old daughter
was in the laurel tree.

806
01:06:17,640 --> 01:06:20,720
She watched her daddy murder a man
in cold blood.

807
01:06:20,840 --> 01:06:23,760
And three, Quince Lincoln
never stole a thing.

808
01:06:23,880 --> 01:06:28,280
My father found that toy soldier
but he was too terrified to tell you.

809
01:06:28,400 --> 01:06:31,680
He had to live with that
for the rest of his sad life.

810
01:06:31,800 --> 01:06:36,800
Maybe you didn't have the balls
to put a stop to this but I do.

811
01:06:37,040 --> 01:06:40,080
It ends with me. We've got four days left,

812
01:06:40,200 --> 01:06:43,680
this is our last appeal
and it's called mitigating circumstances.

813
01:06:43,800 --> 01:06:47,320
Talk to me.

814
01:06:47,840 --> 01:06:50,840
Talk to me, Sam!

815
01:06:52,040 --> 01:06:54,840
I'm tired of talking.

816
01:06:56,360 --> 01:07:01,520
I'm tired of waking up every morning
knowing I'm one day closer to dying.

817
01:07:01,640 --> 01:07:05,360
Tired of living in a cage,
tired of these crappy cigarettes.

818
01:07:05,480 --> 01:07:09,720
I'm just praying I'll die of cancer
before they gas me.

819
01:07:12,760 --> 01:07:16,040
But mostly I'm just tired of waiting.

820
01:07:21,800 --> 01:07:23,520
Just let me rest.

821
01:07:23,640 --> 01:07:27,800
I'm really touched you can share
your feelings with me, Sam,

822
01:07:27,920 --> 01:07:30,240
but at the moment I don't give a damn.

823
01:07:30,360 --> 01:07:35,720
I'm too busy trying to win my case.
Now, start talking!

824
01:07:38,000 --> 01:07:41,960
Here are some synonyms for mitigating -
glossing over,

825
01:07:42,080 --> 01:07:43,600
sugar-coating,

826
01:07:43,720 --> 01:07:45,360
prettifying.

827
01:07:45,480 --> 01:07:48,560
There's nothing pretty
about twin boys being blown to bits,

828
01:07:48,680 --> 01:07:50,920
no glossing over the suicide of their father,

829
01:07:51,040 --> 01:07:53,720
and there's no sugar-coating this fact -

830
01:07:53,840 --> 01:07:58,080
my client is guilty
and he deserves to be punished.

831
01:08:00,040 --> 01:08:03,520
Mens rea. To do the thing.

832
01:08:03,640 --> 01:08:05,760
Sam Cayhall did the thing

833
01:08:05,880 --> 01:08:08,000
but he does not deserve to be murdered

834
01:08:08,120 --> 01:08:11,080
because he was taught from birth
that he had to do the thing.

835
01:08:11,200 --> 01:08:14,200
That is what this court must understand.

836
01:08:14,320 --> 01:08:19,320
He never knew he had any other recourse
but hatred and bigotry and violence.

837
01:08:19,440 --> 01:08:21,800
His uncles and brothers were Klansmen,

838
01:08:21,920 --> 01:08:24,560
his father was a Klansman,
even his grandfather.

839
01:08:24,680 --> 01:08:28,560
His great-grandfather was one
of the co-founders of that hateful group.

840
01:08:28,680 --> 01:08:32,400
I recently saw a photograph of him
at a lynching.

841
01:08:32,520 --> 01:08:35,360
He was ten and it was his third.

842
01:08:36,960 --> 01:08:40,320
Of course, this is awful, it's evil...

843
01:08:40,440 --> 01:08:44,720
but blood and death
were served with Sunday breakfast.

844
01:08:45,080 --> 01:08:49,520
His father was murdered at a funeral.
My client saw it.

845
01:08:51,040 --> 01:08:54,720
As the court is no doubt aware,
my client is also my grandfather.

846
01:08:54,840 --> 01:08:59,400
I'd like now to tell you some warm
and wonderful stories about our family.

847
01:08:59,520 --> 01:09:02,680
Except I don't know any.

848
01:09:02,960 --> 01:09:08,120
In fact, I don't find my grandfather
even remotely wonderful.

849
01:09:08,680 --> 01:09:13,040
But I know this - the very things
that make him so monstrous

850
01:09:13,160 --> 01:09:16,680
are the reasons that mitigate
against this state murdering him.

851
01:09:16,800 --> 01:09:19,200
He was raised by his family and by this state

852
01:09:19,320 --> 01:09:21,640
to become the man that he became.

853
01:09:21,760 --> 01:09:25,880
By the time he was old enough
to choose he didn't have a choice.

854
01:09:26,000 --> 01:09:29,040
This is the tragedy of Sam Cayhall.

855
01:09:30,400 --> 01:09:34,960
It's a tragedy that has destroyed
three lives already.

856
01:09:36,560 --> 01:09:39,320
In the name of mercy...

857
01:09:39,440 --> 01:09:43,480
let it not murder what little is left of his life.

858
01:10:01,920 --> 01:10:04,000
Thank you for seeing me like this.

859
01:10:04,120 --> 01:10:07,120
Why are you here?

860
01:10:08,120 --> 01:10:12,120
I'm hoping you'll ask the governor
to show some mercy.

861
01:10:12,240 --> 01:10:15,000
Tell him you don't want my client to die.

862
01:10:15,120 --> 01:10:19,000
I don't want him to die.
I don't want him to...

863
01:10:19,120 --> 01:10:21,560
but I feel he must.

864
01:10:21,680 --> 01:10:24,240
See, that's not true, it isn't, it...

865
01:10:24,360 --> 01:10:26,280
Your word would carry a lot of weight,

866
01:10:26,400 --> 01:10:29,720
and no one knows more than you
that there's been enough suffering

867
01:10:29,840 --> 01:10:33,560
and it could all end right here, right now.

868
01:10:35,160 --> 01:10:39,920
I didn't take them to nursery school
that morning because I was sick,

869
01:10:40,040 --> 01:10:43,880
so I waved goodbye
from my bedroom window

870
01:10:44,000 --> 01:10:47,160
and watched them
leapfrog off to their death.

871
01:10:47,280 --> 01:10:49,680
Bye, Mommy, I love you!

872
01:10:49,800 --> 01:10:51,920
<i>You see, the whole thing was my fault.</i>

873
01:10:52,040 --> 01:10:54,240
Be good!

874
01:10:56,920 --> 01:10:59,280
- Adam?
- Ma'am?

875
01:10:59,400 --> 01:11:02,800
Why are you really here?

876
01:11:10,960 --> 01:11:16,120
One day I found my father on the floor
in my bedroom with a gun in his hand.

877
01:11:16,240 --> 01:11:21,320
And I remember wondering,
"What are all those towels doing there?"

878
01:11:22,320 --> 01:11:27,800
And then I realised that
he had arranged the towels in a circle...

879
01:11:28,560 --> 01:11:34,040
and very carefully laid down in the centre
so he wouldn't make a mess.

880
01:11:35,440 --> 01:11:38,880
In his note he said that he loved me

881
01:11:39,000 --> 01:11:41,440
and he was sorry and...

882
01:11:41,560 --> 01:11:44,960
he hoped that one day I'd understand.

883
01:11:45,560 --> 01:11:49,360
He told me to take care
of my mom and my sister.

884
01:11:49,880 --> 01:11:53,000
And there was a plastic garbage bag
on the floor.

885
01:11:53,120 --> 01:11:55,080
I was to put the towels in the bag,

886
01:11:55,200 --> 01:11:57,640
clean up the mess and call the police.

887
01:11:57,760 --> 01:12:00,040
"Don't touch the gun," he said.

888
01:12:00,160 --> 01:12:03,400
"Hurry up before the girls get home."

889
01:12:03,800 --> 01:12:08,280
He had picked a day when he knew
I'd be the first one home.

890
01:12:09,760 --> 01:12:12,160
I was ten.

891
01:12:12,440 --> 01:12:17,600
I would dearly love to help you, Adam.
Please know this.

892
01:12:18,400 --> 01:12:23,600
Sam Cayhall destroyed both our families.
Mine just died first.

893
01:12:24,400 --> 01:12:28,280
And I'm sorry but he has to die.

894
01:12:28,400 --> 01:12:30,640
Why?

895
01:12:30,760 --> 01:12:35,560
He has to die because I had champagne
at my birthday party.

896
01:12:35,680 --> 01:12:39,920
He has to die because
a story needs an ending.

897
01:12:41,760 --> 01:12:46,560
He has to die because
I don't care if he had no choice...

898
01:12:46,680 --> 01:12:52,800
he chose to bomb that building...
and my family died.

899
01:12:58,560 --> 01:13:01,600
You know, they were your age then.

900
01:13:03,960 --> 01:13:07,440
And they would have been your age now.

901
01:13:40,560 --> 01:13:43,840
Haven't given up, have you?

902
01:13:45,920 --> 01:13:50,720
Sometimes I just like to see
if I still have what it takes.

903
01:13:50,840 --> 01:13:52,720
Jesus. What are you doing here?

904
01:13:52,840 --> 01:13:57,000
I've been watching you, kid.
You deserve the facts.

905
01:13:57,760 --> 01:14:03,200
Back in '67 I found an old drunk,
he was a dishwasher.

906
01:14:03,400 --> 01:14:07,920
He claimed the night before the bombing
he saw Sam in a diner with another guy.

907
01:14:08,040 --> 01:14:10,120
I need a name.

908
01:14:10,240 --> 01:14:14,160
The description matched a guy
that we always suspected but...

909
01:14:14,280 --> 01:14:16,320
RW.

910
01:14:18,160 --> 01:14:20,960
Rollie Wedge.

911
01:14:23,320 --> 01:14:27,320
A real hater, but smart.
We could never tie him to anything.

912
01:14:27,440 --> 01:14:28,840
Where is he now?

913
01:14:28,960 --> 01:14:32,120
They've gathered - sort of like a reunion -

914
01:14:32,240 --> 01:14:35,600
the night before the big execution
and all that.

915
01:14:35,720 --> 01:14:39,520
I figure if he's here, he's there.

916
01:15:09,320 --> 01:15:14,160
...slapped the hell out of him,
he took a lickin', didn't he?

917
01:15:14,280 --> 01:15:16,280
Looking forward to...

918
01:15:40,720 --> 01:15:43,600
Outside! Come on.

919
01:16:39,200 --> 01:16:41,960
Get away from that boy.

920
01:16:42,080 --> 01:16:44,880
Get.

921
01:16:45,920 --> 01:16:48,720
Thank you. Oh, God.

922
01:16:50,760 --> 01:16:54,120
Thank you. I appreciate it.

923
01:16:54,240 --> 01:16:57,400
You do?

924
01:17:03,800 --> 01:17:05,240
Rollie Wedge.

925
01:17:05,360 --> 01:17:08,800
One of the many names
that I've been called.

926
01:17:08,920 --> 01:17:11,440
What do you think you're doing here?

927
01:17:11,560 --> 01:17:14,320
You planted the bomb that killed those kids.

928
01:17:14,440 --> 01:17:18,120
Were you planning a citizen's arrest?

929
01:17:18,240 --> 01:17:20,160
I just want to hear you admit it.

930
01:17:20,280 --> 01:17:22,360
Delusion, Mr Hall.

931
01:17:22,480 --> 01:17:26,120
You're looking for a clean "yes"
so you can identify,

932
01:17:26,240 --> 01:17:29,560
quantify, organise a concept of evil.

933
01:17:29,680 --> 01:17:33,080
If I did it then I'm the evil

934
01:17:33,200 --> 01:17:35,720
and I can be culled from the flock,

935
01:17:35,840 --> 01:17:39,240
removed, separated, destroyed.

936
01:17:39,360 --> 01:17:40,960
Evil can be destroyed

937
01:17:41,080 --> 01:17:46,840
and all you good people can feel safe
in the cocoon of your denial.

938
01:17:46,960 --> 01:17:49,960
- Sam says you're his people.
- We are one.

939
01:17:50,080 --> 01:17:52,400
Is this how you treat your people?

940
01:17:52,520 --> 01:17:55,760
Let 'em take a fall for you?

941
01:17:56,320 --> 01:17:58,880
What about loyalty?

942
01:17:59,000 --> 01:18:02,760
What about the truth?

943
01:18:07,320 --> 01:18:11,560
The truth, based on your laws, Attorney Hall,

944
01:18:11,680 --> 01:18:16,160
is that Sam Cayhall is guilty
and has been sentenced to death.

945
01:18:16,280 --> 01:18:19,200
Perhaps it's time for you
to show some loyalty

946
01:18:19,320 --> 01:18:22,000
and let justice be served.

947
01:18:22,120 --> 01:18:24,920
And after it is...

948
01:18:25,240 --> 01:18:28,160
always look behind you.

949
01:18:29,040 --> 01:18:31,840
Always.

950
01:18:45,640 --> 01:18:49,160
- He's probably still there.
- And?

951
01:18:49,280 --> 01:18:52,840
If Sam were tried as an accomplice,
the most he'd get is 20 years.

952
01:18:52,960 --> 01:18:54,800
You said you wanted new information.

953
01:18:54,920 --> 01:19:00,440
With all due respect, this is hardly
compelling evidence of anything.

954
01:19:00,560 --> 01:19:03,360
Grant a stay, give me more time.

955
01:19:04,920 --> 01:19:06,640
All right, men, listen up.

956
01:19:06,760 --> 01:19:11,400
0800 hours, I hereby activate
the Emergency Operations Centre.

957
01:19:11,520 --> 01:19:13,640
This institution is on lockdown status.

958
01:19:13,760 --> 01:19:17,920
<i>I expect each of you
to discharge your duty accordingly.</i>

959
01:19:18,040 --> 01:19:20,440
<i>No second-guessing, no improvising.</i>

960
01:19:20,560 --> 01:19:24,320
This execution will take place in 16 hours.

961
01:20:23,040 --> 01:20:25,960
What you did to those babies...

962
01:20:27,840 --> 01:20:31,360
no one could ever forgive you for.

963
01:20:33,440 --> 01:20:36,600
What you did to me...

964
01:20:37,880 --> 01:20:40,680
and Eddie...

965
01:20:43,160 --> 01:20:46,320
I've got to.

966
01:20:53,960 --> 01:20:56,760
Not for you, old man...

967
01:21:00,480 --> 01:21:03,880
for me.

968
01:21:22,360 --> 01:21:25,280
Eddie said...

969
01:21:28,080 --> 01:21:31,400
you'd never have shot Joe Lincoln...

970
01:21:32,280 --> 01:21:35,520
if I'd have cried out for you not to.

971
01:21:37,400 --> 01:21:40,200
Is that why you came here?

972
01:21:44,080 --> 01:21:46,880
No.

973
01:21:54,320 --> 01:21:57,840
Would you still have shot him?

974
01:22:00,520 --> 01:22:03,920
Yeah, yeah.

975
01:22:31,520 --> 01:22:35,720
<i>The Fifth Circuit Court of Appeals
denied Sam Cayhall's last appeal.</i>

976
01:22:35,840 --> 01:22:38,760
<i>The US Supreme Court
will rule later today on his fate.</i>

977
01:22:38,880 --> 01:22:43,280
<i>If they deny, Governor David McAllister
will be his last chance.</i>

978
01:22:43,400 --> 01:22:46,320
<i>The execution is set
for 12:01 tomorrow morning.</i>

979
01:22:46,440 --> 01:22:50,000
<i>Stephanie Bell Flynt, WLBT News.</i>

980
01:22:54,800 --> 01:22:59,600
Got a light, yeah?

981
01:23:15,480 --> 01:23:18,480
Sam?

982
01:23:21,080 --> 01:23:24,600
Met some of your real people last night.

983
01:23:25,640 --> 01:23:29,920
Real interesting group, your real people.

984
01:23:32,960 --> 01:23:35,960
Especially Rollie Wedge.

985
01:23:36,560 --> 01:23:39,840
Rollie Wedge.

986
01:23:40,880 --> 01:23:43,760
He was real interesting.

987
01:24:01,080 --> 01:24:03,000
I have to talk to the guards.

988
01:24:03,120 --> 01:24:05,920
Rack up Sam.

989
01:24:15,440 --> 01:24:18,880
You look a lot like your brother.

990
01:24:52,600 --> 01:24:55,880
I came to pay my respects, Sam.

991
01:24:57,000 --> 01:24:58,880
Say goodbye.

992
01:24:59,000 --> 01:25:03,240
Make sure you're still strong.

993
01:25:08,600 --> 01:25:11,440
I saw those two little kids.

994
01:25:12,480 --> 01:25:14,880
They was in the window.

995
01:25:16,120 --> 01:25:18,920
That was a mistake.

996
01:25:19,480 --> 01:25:23,800
We kept two little Jews
from growing up into big Jews.

997
01:25:23,920 --> 01:25:26,440
When their nigger-loving father
killed hisself

998
01:25:26,560 --> 01:25:31,400
it was like dropping
a little hook-nosed pebble in a pond.

999
01:25:32,080 --> 01:25:36,800
The ripples went out with a message
for all the world to see -

1000
01:25:37,360 --> 01:25:40,800
the Jew is weak.

1001
01:25:41,400 --> 01:25:44,000
How do you figure that for a mistake?

1002
01:25:44,120 --> 01:25:46,400
Weren't supposed to be no killing.

1003
01:25:46,520 --> 01:25:48,920
Don't go soft, Sam.

1004
01:25:49,040 --> 01:25:52,000
The day is coming.

1005
01:25:54,160 --> 01:25:58,240
I wish you could stick around to see it,
buddy, it's coming.

1006
01:25:58,360 --> 01:26:01,040
Every day, more people open their eyes

1007
01:26:01,160 --> 01:26:03,800
and see the only thing wrong
with this country

1008
01:26:03,920 --> 01:26:09,520
is we've gone against the laws of nature,
God's law.

1009
01:26:11,640 --> 01:26:15,880
Only the strong have a right to survive.

1010
01:26:16,000 --> 01:26:19,520
And now, finally...

1011
01:26:19,920 --> 01:26:21,520
those not worthy -

1012
01:26:21,640 --> 01:26:26,960
the Jew, the African,
he who lies with another man -

1013
01:26:27,080 --> 01:26:29,920
they're all digging their own graves

1014
01:26:30,040 --> 01:26:32,320
and when we pile them in there

1015
01:26:32,440 --> 01:26:34,880
I'll drink a toast to you, Sam,

1016
01:26:35,000 --> 01:26:37,840
and I'll piss it out on their dead faces.

1017
01:26:37,960 --> 01:26:39,520
No.

1018
01:26:39,640 --> 01:26:42,680
You've been a good and loyal soldier, Sam.

1019
01:26:42,800 --> 01:26:45,640
Go with the dignity that is yours,

1020
01:26:45,760 --> 01:26:51,680
don't be confused by that little boy
who's got his daddy's weak blood in him.

1021
01:26:51,800 --> 01:26:54,720
He ain't pure, he ain't us.

1022
01:26:54,840 --> 01:27:00,160
No, you son of a bitch. You son of a bitch.

1023
01:27:00,400 --> 01:27:03,680
I ain't you. I ain't you!

1024
01:27:03,800 --> 01:27:06,280
You touch him, I kill you.

1025
01:27:07,560 --> 01:27:11,360
I'll rip your head off.
I'll kill you, you son of a bitch.

1026
01:27:11,480 --> 01:27:13,240
- You know who this is?
- Your brother.

1027
01:27:13,360 --> 01:27:16,760
No, he ain't my brother.
You ain't my brother!

1028
01:27:16,880 --> 01:27:19,240
- Get out of here.
- I'll be praying for you.

1029
01:27:19,360 --> 01:27:21,880
You go to hell, you son of a bitch.

1030
01:27:22,000 --> 01:27:24,960
- Go to hell!
- I'll be praying for you.

1031
01:27:37,560 --> 01:27:40,240
Rack Sam.

1032
01:27:44,800 --> 01:27:47,680
No word from the courts.

1033
01:28:01,400 --> 01:28:06,800
I'd like you to mail this for me.
If you would.

1034
01:28:08,840 --> 01:28:12,040
I don't have the addresses.

1035
01:28:25,000 --> 01:28:28,320
Don't give up, Sam.

1036
01:28:31,560 --> 01:28:34,360
There is one other thing.

1037
01:28:45,400 --> 01:28:47,760
Take that.

1038
01:28:53,520 --> 01:28:56,320
Rack Sam.

1039
01:29:02,640 --> 01:29:04,320
It's the Supreme Court.

1040
01:29:04,440 --> 01:29:08,400
The coffee's French Market,
just like you asked.

1041
01:29:08,520 --> 01:29:11,320
Thank you.

1042
01:29:14,320 --> 01:29:17,440
Rack back.

1043
01:29:21,200 --> 01:29:24,000
Adam Hall.

1044
01:29:29,200 --> 01:29:32,360
No. OK.

1045
01:29:42,560 --> 01:29:45,000
It ain't over, Sam.

1046
01:29:45,120 --> 01:29:48,120
It ain't over.

1047
01:29:59,720 --> 01:30:01,720
<i>The United States Supreme Court</i>

1048
01:30:01,840 --> 01:30:07,200
<i>has denied a flurry of last-minute appeals
on behalf of Sam Cayhall.</i>

1049
01:30:20,240 --> 01:30:24,560
Gas his ass! Gas his ass!

1050
01:30:29,000 --> 01:30:30,520
Hurry. Let's go.

1051
01:30:30,640 --> 01:30:33,200
Go.

1052
01:30:33,960 --> 01:30:36,040
Cayhall signed the request.

1053
01:30:36,160 --> 01:30:40,120
Goodman's in court now asking to open up
the Sovereignty Commission files.

1054
01:30:40,240 --> 01:30:41,880
What should we do?

1055
01:30:42,000 --> 01:30:45,600
I don't recall being asked to do anything.
Let's see what's in there.

1056
01:30:45,720 --> 01:30:49,120
It suggests an accomplice
to the Kramer bombing, for one.

1057
01:30:49,240 --> 01:30:51,640
Some far-right crazy named Rollie Wedge.

1058
01:30:51,760 --> 01:30:54,600
How the hell do you know that?

1059
01:30:59,080 --> 01:31:02,400
We'll discuss it later.
Now, if you'll excuse us?

1060
01:31:02,520 --> 01:31:06,440
- You were saying?
- I don't think it'll work.

1061
01:31:06,560 --> 01:31:10,920
There are other names. Some familiar.

1062
01:31:11,440 --> 01:31:15,600
Knowing in advance might be very useful.

1063
01:31:31,160 --> 01:31:33,960
It's the Governor, sir.

1064
01:31:34,160 --> 01:31:35,280
Hello, Governor.

1065
01:31:35,400 --> 01:31:39,920
<i>Senator, Sam Cayhall's attorneys are trying
to get some Sovereignty files released</i>

1066
01:31:40,040 --> 01:31:42,720
<i>that you and your colleagues
might not appreciate.</i>

1067
01:31:42,840 --> 01:31:46,120
<i>I got a proposition for y'all
but you have to act fast.</i>

1068
01:31:46,240 --> 01:31:48,880
Can't go home if you're going by the mill

1069
01:31:49,000 --> 01:31:51,120
Cos the bridge washed out
at the bottom of the hill

1070
01:31:51,240 --> 01:31:53,760
Big Creek's up and the Little Creek's level

1071
01:31:53,880 --> 01:31:57,760
Plough my corn with a double shovel...

1072
01:31:59,320 --> 01:32:02,240
These are for you, Cayhall.

1073
01:32:08,920 --> 01:32:12,760
I can offer you a sedative if you'd like.

1074
01:32:14,600 --> 01:32:17,400
All right.

1075
01:32:18,240 --> 01:32:22,080
Then you'd best start changing.
I'll be back in 30 minutes.

1076
01:32:22,200 --> 01:32:25,600
Don't be late.

1077
01:32:33,080 --> 01:32:35,040
Pull off your coat, throw it in the corner

1078
01:32:35,160 --> 01:32:39,120
Don't see why you don't stay a little longer

1079
01:32:39,440 --> 01:32:43,240
Old mule and the grasshopper
eating ice cream...

1080
01:33:12,640 --> 01:33:16,240
Gas his ass, gas his ass!

1081
01:33:25,840 --> 01:33:28,880
Rack up Cayhall.

1082
01:33:59,040 --> 01:34:01,840
It's all right.

1083
01:34:07,920 --> 01:34:10,480
Appeal's on the 28th, now don't forget.

1084
01:34:10,600 --> 01:34:13,320
I left your papers with Barry
in the law library.

1085
01:34:13,440 --> 01:34:14,800
Thanks, Sam.

1086
01:34:14,920 --> 01:34:18,840
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
the governor of the state of Mississippi,</i>

1087
01:34:18,960 --> 01:34:23,120
<i>the Honourable David Allen McAllister.</i>

1088
01:34:29,480 --> 01:34:31,640
Tonight...

1089
01:34:31,760 --> 01:34:34,680
the Supreme Court of the United States

1090
01:34:34,800 --> 01:34:40,760
rejected all appeals
filed on behalf of Sam Cayhall.

1091
01:34:43,120 --> 01:34:46,400
<i>So, at this moment of truth</i>

1092
01:34:46,520 --> 01:34:49,800
<i>I must face the terrible burden
of this office</i>

1093
01:34:49,920 --> 01:34:53,680
<i>that is mine and mine alone.</i>

1094
01:34:53,880 --> 01:34:56,200
<i>The question for me tonight is,</i>

1095
01:34:56,320 --> 01:35:00,480
<i>who is David Allen McAllister</i>

1096
01:35:00,600 --> 01:35:02,760
<i>to imagine in his finest hour...</i>

1097
01:35:02,880 --> 01:35:05,400
- See you, JB.
- See you soon, Sam.

1098
01:35:05,520 --> 01:35:10,120
<i>- ...wiser than the jury and the 47 judges...
- Spit in their eye, Sam.</i>

1099
01:35:10,240 --> 01:35:14,520
<i>...who have reviewed this case
over the last 16 years?</i>

1100
01:35:14,640 --> 01:35:18,560
<i>- Sam. Remember the Lord is with you.
- The answer's clear.</i>

1101
01:35:18,680 --> 01:35:20,840
<i>In the matter of life and death,</i>

1102
01:35:20,960 --> 01:35:26,400
<i>none among us are more knowing
than our system of justice.</i>

1103
01:35:27,200 --> 01:35:31,120
<i>Tonight, however,
information has come to us suggesting</i>

1104
01:35:31,240 --> 01:35:35,080
<i>Mr Cayhall may not have acted alone
in this heinous crime.</i>

1105
01:35:35,200 --> 01:35:39,520
<i>Now if these allegations prove to be true,</i>

1106
01:35:39,640 --> 01:35:43,480
<i>rest assured, anyone found to be involved</i>

1107
01:35:43,600 --> 01:35:47,640
<i>will be prosecuted
to the fullest extent of the law.</i>

1108
01:35:47,760 --> 01:35:49,800
However,

1109
01:35:49,920 --> 01:35:54,320
no matter how many additional people
may be implicated in the future,

1110
01:35:54,440 --> 01:35:59,440
it does not change a fundamental fact -

1111
01:35:59,760 --> 01:36:02,640
Sam Cayhall is guilty as charged

1112
01:36:02,760 --> 01:36:06,520
and Sam Cayhall must pay the price.

1113
01:36:13,240 --> 01:36:15,040
So it...

1114
01:36:15,160 --> 01:36:20,160
It is with the greatest humility

1115
01:36:20,280 --> 01:36:25,280
that I bow in deference
to that great lady, Justice.

1116
01:36:26,000 --> 01:36:28,560
At one minute past midnight,

1117
01:36:28,680 --> 01:36:31,280
Sam Cayhall will meet his maker.

1118
01:36:31,400 --> 01:36:35,800
<i>The final judgment will truly be His.</i>

1119
01:36:40,200 --> 01:36:43,120
<i>To the family of the victims...</i>

1120
01:36:43,240 --> 01:36:48,840
<i>we say nothing can replace
your great and terrible loss.</i>

1121
01:36:48,960 --> 01:36:53,400
<i>Revenge will never lessen
the unfillable void</i>

1122
01:36:53,520 --> 01:36:56,240
<i>left by those now gone.</i>

1123
01:36:56,360 --> 01:36:59,560
And we pray with you...

1124
01:37:00,240 --> 01:37:04,080
that God may grant us
the strength and the courage

1125
01:37:04,200 --> 01:37:10,240
to prevent crimes like this
from ever again darkening our soul

1126
01:37:10,360 --> 01:37:13,320
with the blood of the innocent.

1127
01:37:15,800 --> 01:37:20,280
Good night and God bless America.

1128
01:37:24,720 --> 01:37:26,800
Kid, don't.

1129
01:37:26,920 --> 01:37:29,320
Don't try to save me any more.

1130
01:37:29,440 --> 01:37:35,640
I know someplace inside you,
you're trying to stir up some miracle.

1131
01:37:43,400 --> 01:37:46,200
We can't forget who Sam Cayhall is

1132
01:37:46,320 --> 01:37:49,120
or the kind of thinking that he represents.

1133
01:37:49,240 --> 01:37:51,440
I'm sure you haven't.

1134
01:37:51,560 --> 01:37:54,120
- And the other names?
- Useful information.

1135
01:37:54,240 --> 01:37:57,160
It'll help us effect
some real change next session.

1136
01:37:57,280 --> 01:37:59,880
Isn't that why we're doing this job?

1137
01:38:00,000 --> 01:38:04,000
All progress is a negotiation, Nora.

1138
01:39:02,360 --> 01:39:05,520
Of all the people and things
I hated my whole life,

1139
01:39:05,640 --> 01:39:09,360
the one I hated most was me.

1140
01:39:12,920 --> 01:39:16,680
I was given free entry into this world
to make of it whatever I could.

1141
01:39:16,800 --> 01:39:20,280
I've been sitting here for 16 years.

1142
01:39:21,000 --> 01:39:25,800
I was thinking, I...
I never did anybody any good.

1143
01:39:31,000 --> 01:39:33,800
Till you came down.

1144
01:39:40,640 --> 01:39:45,000
See, if I'm gonna be proud of you,
I got to be proud of your daddy.

1145
01:39:45,120 --> 01:39:49,120
He wasn't a weak guy, he was strong.

1146
01:39:51,160 --> 01:39:54,920
Strong enough to get away...

1147
01:39:55,040 --> 01:39:59,440
strong enough to give you
whatever it is that you got.

1148
01:40:02,320 --> 01:40:04,520
If he was able to give that to you,

1149
01:40:04,640 --> 01:40:09,360
I reckon this old man must have passed on
something good to him.

1150
01:40:14,920 --> 01:40:17,720
And I didn't know that.

1151
01:40:33,960 --> 01:40:36,760
I'm ready.

1152
01:40:46,320 --> 01:40:49,920
You come on in, we been waiting for you.

1153
01:41:01,360 --> 01:41:04,560
Do you know where you're going?

1154
01:42:18,080 --> 01:42:20,880
Moving right along.

1155
01:43:46,520 --> 01:43:50,120
What the fuck is going on, man?

1156
01:44:45,880 --> 01:44:47,800
Sam, this is your death warrant.

1157
01:44:47,920 --> 01:44:50,520
You know I'm required by law
to read it to you.

1158
01:44:50,640 --> 01:44:54,000
"We, the jury, find unanimously
and beyond a reasonable doubt

1159
01:44:54,120 --> 01:44:56,480
the following aggravating circumstances.

1160
01:44:56,600 --> 01:45:00,200
The capital murder
was committed during a felony.

1161
01:45:00,320 --> 01:45:03,800
The capital murder was especially heinous,
atrocious and cruel.

1162
01:45:03,920 --> 01:45:07,640
We, the jury, find unanimously
and beyond a reasonable doubt

1163
01:45:07,760 --> 01:45:11,560
the defendant Sam Cayhall
should be put to death by lethal gas

1164
01:45:11,680 --> 01:45:14,840
at the Mississippi State Penitentiary.

1165
01:45:14,960 --> 01:45:18,440
The 13th day of April, 1996."

1166
01:45:18,920 --> 01:45:20,280
Come on!

1167
01:45:20,400 --> 01:45:22,200
And no stays.

1168
01:45:22,320 --> 01:45:25,280
Is there any reason why
this execution should not proceed?

1169
01:45:25,400 --> 01:45:28,200
No.

1170
01:45:28,560 --> 01:45:31,320
Any final words, Mr Cayhall?

1171
01:48:08,240 --> 01:48:11,160
Maybe the ghosts are gone, Lee.

1172
01:48:14,800 --> 01:48:17,600
Maybe.

1173
01:48:21,960 --> 01:48:24,840
Thank you, Adam.

